column1: California roots.  Global  reach. Atkinson, Andelson, Loya, Ruud & Romo has been committed to serving our public- and private-sector clients since 1979.  With over 200 attorneys across nine offices throughout the state, we'll meet you wherever you are, for whatever needs that arise.

Legal experts.  Trusted  advisors. We've cultivated a deep bench of talented attorneys who have been continuously recognized as leaders in their fields. Many have served as teachers, HR professionals, architects, and more. Their expertise is not just legal but experiential.

Your challenges are unique.  Our  solutions  are too. At AALRR, our clients are unique... and their cases are, too. We believe in tailor-made solutions, not a cookie-cutter approach.  When it comes to your case, we leave no stone unturned. And we are always available to answer your questions or concerns.

Strength through  Diversity . Law360  named AALRR the top law firm in the country for minority equity partners and minority attorneys in general.  At AALRR, diversity isn't just something we say, it's something we do—both within our office walls and in our wider communities.

column1: Alameda County, Santa Clara County & Contra Costa County Creditors' Rights Attorney Debt Collection and Creditors' Rights Lawyer in Alameda County, CA If you are facing a legal matter involving  creditors' rights ,  debt collection ,  commercial litigation  or  business litigation , you will need an attorney at your side experienced with civil cases who can zealously and effectively protect your rights and interests as a creditor. Stephen G. Opperwall is a highly experienced civil litigation lawyer who has approximately 40 years of legal experience in this field. Attorney Opperwall first received the designation of ""Board Certified Specialist in Creditors' Rights"" in 1997 from the Academy of Commercial and Bankruptcy Law Specialists and the Commercial Law League of America. By 2003, the certification functions of the Academy had been taken over by the American Board of Certification, and Mr. Opperwall was recertified at that time. Mr. Opperwall's certification continued into 2010, by which time he had been named to the list of Super Lawyers of Northern California in creditors rights, bankruptcy, and business/commercial litigation. The status of Certified Specialist in Creditors' Rights has been held by fewer than 10 attorneys in California.

column2: Mr. Opperwall has also been named to the highly exclusive and honored list of Super Lawyers of Northern California. This list is reserved for the top 5% of attorneys in the area. Mr. Opperwall was first named to the Super Lawyers of Northern California list starting in 2007, and virtually every year since that time. He has also been named to the Super Lawyers Corporate Counsel Edition. Mr. Opperwall's areas of designation on the Super Lawyers of Northern California list are creditors' rights, bankruptcy, and business litigation. There are only approximately 40 attorneys on the Super Lawyers of Northern California list in creditors' rights, out of nearly 300,000 attorneys in California. Mr. Opperwall has also been named to the Multi Million Dollar Advocates Forum, an exclusive group of attorneys who have recovered $2,000,000 or more for at least one client, something which Mr. Opperwall has done multiple times. The Multi Million Dollar Advocates Forum has only 4,000 members nationwide. Mr. Opperwall has been named to the exclusive list of the Top 100 Bet-The-Company Litigators in: Bet-The-Company Litigation, Commercial Litigation, General Civil litigation, and High Stakes Litigation. Mr. Opperwall has recovered many tens of millions of dollars for clients in the form of judgments, settlements, and recoveries, with multiple cases involving well in excess of $2,000,000. At the Law Offices of Stephen G. Opperwall, clients can expect to receive personal attention and service through every step of the legal process, as well as fiercely loyal and tireless representation both inside and outside of the courtroom. The firm represents clients in civil litigation focusing on  creditors' rights , as well as a range of other issues in business law, commercial law, and bankruptcy. Your initial consultation with Northern California creditors' rights lawyer Stephen Opperwall is free, and you can count on receiving honest, valuable advice so you can make the right decision about your case and legal counsel.

column1: Gaining Control Over Accounts Receivable With a Debt Collection Lawyer When you are dealing with an issue regarding debt collection, direct intervention by an experienced creditors' rights attorney can help ensure that you recover your money fast. Outstanding accounts receivable can create a number of problems for any company, large or small. Debtors may be less likely to ignore a letter or other communication from an attorney than they would the vendor themselves. With extensive experience in debt collection litigation and as a creditors' rights specialist, Stephen G. Opperwall understands how to deal with the many aspects of debt collection. For examples, refer to the links for  Areas of Law  and for  Types of Procedures & Proceedings . You have many avenues of legal recourse that can be explored to help you gain control over outstanding debt.

Practice Areas - Creditors' Rights, Civil and Debt Collection The Law Offices of Stephen G. Opperwall can assist you with expert legal services and litigation in areas including, but not limited to, the following: Creditors' Rights Creditors' Remedies Debt Collection Breach of Contract Commercial Collections Business Litigation Commercial Litigation Promissory Notes Accounts Receivable Collection Secured Transactions Successor Liability Breach of Fiduciary Duty Implied Covenant of Good Faith & Fair Dealing Fraudulent Transfer Leases Real Property Disputes Broker Disputes Bankruptcy (Representing Creditors) Labor/Employment Disputes Construction Disputes Mechanics' Liens The Law Offices of Stephen G. Opperwall has a main office location in Pleasanton as well as one in Santa Clara, and takes on cases throughout all of Northern California. Whether you are seeking representation in Santa Clara County, Contra Costa County or Alameda County, the firm can assist you.

column1: Consult Attorney Stephen G. Opperwall Today In the face of a legal matter that has the potential to significantly impact you financially, personally and professionally, your choice of legal counsel is important. Your attorney may directly impact the outcome of your case, particularly if he or she is incompetent or inexperienced. At the Law Offices of Stephen G. Opperwall, you can feel confident that your case is in experienced hands. Board certified in creditors' rights and with almost four decades of civil litigation experience, Attorney Opperwall is a wise choice. Call our firm at (925) 417-0300 or  contact us   online for your case evaluation.

column6: Fighting for the underdog  for over 50 years. “ Nothing can stop the power of a committed and determined people to make a difference in our society. ”

California roots.  National reach. “California is a place of invention, a place of courage, a place of vision, a place of the future. People who made California what it is were willing to take risks, think outside convention, and build.”
Principle. Commitment.  Hard Work. Justice. ""The most difficult thing is the decision to act, the rest is merely tenacity.""

A Legacy of Results. CPM is a law firm built on a foundation of deeply held principles and commitment. CPM’s shared values are a commitment to justice, hard work, and a promise to deliver true rights to their clients and a just society.
Built on relationships.  Fueled by justice. ""Whether it is a friendship or a relationship, all bonds are built on trust. Without it, you have nothing.""

column5: A San Francisco Bay Area Estate & Trust Planning Firm

column6: O’Donnell & Associates assists clients all over the San Francisco Bay Area with Estate Planning, Probate & Trust Estate Administration,and Special Needs Planning.

column1: Our firm assists clients with various aspects of Estate Planning, such as:

column7: Matthew O’Donnell has been an estate planning attorney for over 35 years with client throughout in the San Francisco Bay Area. His firm has helped more than 10,000 families plan their estates. Although Matt began his legal career as a litigator, his charitable work with senior organizations inspired him to transform his practice to exclusively helping individuals, spouses, partners and families manage their complex and personal estate planning issues. His firm emphasizes “life planning” to prevent Court intrusion and/or control in the event of incapacity, and to protect the estates of surviving spouses, partners and children from creditors, predators and marital conflicts. He also helps special needs, disabled, and elderly clients with public-benefits planning.

column10: We would be pleased to hear from you, so contact our San Francisco Bay Area Estate and Trust Planning Law Firm via telephone or email with your questions, comments or concerns. Alternatively, we would be happy to set up an appointment for a  consultation . For more information contact:  marykay@estateandtrustplanning.com

column1: We assist clients all over the San Francisco Bay Area & Silicon Valley. Our office is in Menlo Park, California. Please call Mary Kay for an appointment 650-853-7183.

#comp-kehivay91{visibility:hidden !important;} top of page Kathryn N. Richter, Esq.

925.683.2918 Kathryn Richter is an independent arbitrator and mediator, with over 30 years experience resolving complex commercial, construction, energy, energy, professional liability, real estate, employment, insurance, product liability, personal injury, product design and manufacturing, intellectual property interests, insolvency and tort matters. With a long history as both an advocate and neutral in domestic and international disputes, Ms. Richter focuses on managing the dispute resolution process to limit time, cost, and risk. Kathryn's history as an advocate, arbitrator, mediator, and special master includes resolution of disputes at the transaction, pre-litigation, litigation and appellate stages. With expertise in business and law, she brings a unique understanding of the risk paradigm that garners buy-in and facilitates resolution. Since 1988, Ms. Richter has successfully managed 1700+ high-stakes, multi-party disputes to resolution, with attentive preparation, a proactive style and dedication to the resolution process. Licensed in and admitted to all California courts. Also admitted to the U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals, 9th Circuit; U.S. District Court for the Northern, Eastern, Central and Southern Districts of California, the Supreme Court of the United States, and numerous  pro hac vice  admissions. Ms. Richter is a contributor to the domestic and international ADR communities; she is available for appointment in any location.     San Francisco - Houston Kathryn's CV Kathryn@RichterADR.com  Richter ADR, LLC Practice Areas & Case Experience ADA Disability

Using experience, skill and judgment, the Ramsey Law Group, a business law firm, will help you with your business legal needs. Our business attorneys work to understand your business and personal goals in addition to your legal situation you now face. As a result, you will find yourself well protected legally and empowered to meet your business objectives. The Ramsey Law Group is responsive, pragmatic and determined to help you succeed.

With over 100 years of collective experience, the attorneys at Ramsey Law Group respond to clients with reliable advice at a reasonable cost. Perhaps more importantly, we see beyond our role as a service provider. We are a committed partner — constantly working to provide added value.

We have successfully solved client concerns in a variety of industries including technology, construction, real estate, and manufacturing. This versatility in industry experience affords us a broad scope and offer thoughtful strategies for use in the care of your business and your transactions, including mergers & acquisitions, contract negotiations, and intellectual property protection.
What Our Clients are Saying “Thank you Bruce! I’m very grateful that I’m able to work with you and your team of professionals!” – Matt C.
“You are the Ferrari of law firms” – Rudy B.

Responsive Using experience, skill and judgment, the Ramsey Law Group, a business law firm, will help you with your business legal needs. Our business attorneys work to understand your business and personal goals in addition to your legal situation you now face. As a result, you will find yourself well protected legally and empowered to meet your business objectives. The Ramsey Law Group is responsive, pragmatic and determined to help you succeed.

Reliable With over 100 years of collective experience, the attorneys at Ramsey Law Group respond to clients with reliable advice at a reasonable cost. Perhaps more importantly, we see beyond our role as a service provider. We are a committed partner — constantly working to provide added value.

Reasonable We have successfully solved client concerns in a variety of industries including technology, construction, real estate, and manufacturing. This versatility in industry experience affords us a broad scope and offer thoughtful strategies for use in the care of your business and your transactions, including mergers & acquisitions, contract negotiations, and intellectual property protection.

Business Formation  Mergers & Acquisitions  Contracts (Negotiation & Formation)  Trademarks & Copyrights  Employment (Compliance, Counseling & Disputes)  Intellectual Property Protection  Telecommunications

We are a responsive and pragmatic law firm that will work to help you succeed. Our attorneys will work in close cooperation with you to clarify your objectives, help you understand likely outcomes and support you in solving a variety of legal issues under the guidance of Business Law and Contract expert Bruce Ramsey.
At the Ramsey Law Group, we can represent you through the many phases of business, from startup to preparing for management transitions or sales.

We have successfully solved client concerns in a variety of industries including technology, construction, real estate, and manufacturing. This versatility in industry experience affords us a broad scope and offer thoughtful strategies for use in the care of your business and your transactions, including mergers & acquisitions, contract negotiations, and intellectual property protection.
Some of our services that cover business litigation include property damage,  lease disputes, construction remedies, land use, and corporate governance.

We realize your situation is our priority; if you would like to review a few of our previous successes, click here.  If you would like to learn more about our legal services, contact us today to schedule a consultation.

column1: Goodman Neuman Hamilton LLP represents Fortune 500 companies and others in civil litigation and appeals throughout California. With 12 lawyers based in San Francisco, GNH combines paramount client service with aggressive, creative, and efficient handling of cases.

The firm’s partners—who have conducted over 100 jury trials—have been recognized as outstanding advocates by clients and colleagues. Accolades include being named among San Francisco Bay Area’s best lawyers by Super Lawyers Magazine and San Francisco magazine, induction into the American Board of Trial Advocates, and receiving the highest rating (AV) awarded by Martindale-Hubbell.

The firm handles a wide variety of civil litigation, including accounting malpractice, construction defect, personal injury, medical malpractice, dental malpractice, and insurance coverage cases. The firm’s clients include individuals, small and mid-sized businesses, insurance companies and other corporations and entities, including Home Depot, McKesson Corporation, River City Bank, Armanino LLP, and The Regents of the University of California.

Your portal to construction law offering consulting services, publications and informational links.

Consulting services:  Construction law consulting services by leading authority in the field. Advice for novice or experienced lawyers, design professionals, contractors, insurers, and owners. Put more than three decades of construction law research, writing and teaching on your side by using the consulting services of Marc M. Schneier.

Publications:     Over several decades, Marc M. Schneier’s publications have educated practitioners, academics, and students about the intricacies of construction law. Publications for practitioners include   Construction Litigation Reporter  (Thomson Reuters/West) and  Construction Accident Law  (ABA 1999). His most recent textbooks for law schools and engineering departments, co-authored with Justin Sweet, are  Construction Law for Design Professionals, Construction Managers, and Contractors  (Cengage Learning 2015) and  Legal Aspects of Architecture, Engineering and the Construction Process  (Cengage Learning 9th ed. 2013).
Teaching:  Marc M. Schneier was an Adjunct Professor of Construction Law at the University of San Francisco School of Law.
Links:  Sites of interest for construction law practitioners and students.

column1: Ken Sigelman J.D, M.D has won numerous awards as a trial lawyer and has established himself among peers and clients alike as a highly-skilled litigator who has decades of experience winning cases for his clients.

Kenneth M. Sigelman & Associates’ story spans 70+ years of combined experience, includes the knowledge of a Lawyer-MD, and is rich with scores of client successes in Medical Malpractice and Serious Injury.

Having seen serious personal injury from the other side of the coin as a medical doctor, Ken Sigelman J.D., M.D has an empathy few lawyers possess. The firm’s clients are far more to it than just cases.

Ken Sigelman J.D., M.D., an expert medical malpractice and serious injury lawyer in California, has more than 20 years experience litigating serious personal injury, medical malpractice, and wrongful death cases before juries on behalf of his clients. He is a medical doctor and has an intimate understanding of the field of medicine that only a small handful of practicing lawyers possess. This medical background allows him to fight for you with a foundation of medical knowledge and legal clout that few personal injury and medical malpractice lawyers in San Diego or California can match. If you have been a victim of a personal injury or medical malpractice, it takes a personal injury lawyer with an understanding of California law, knowledge, experience, and commitment to achieve justice and obtain fair compensation.
San Diego Medical Malpractice & Serious Personal Injury Lawyers

There are few practicing attorneys that are also medical doctors. Ken Sigelman J.D., M.D. brings a thorough understanding of medical malpractice claims not only as an attorney, but also as a licensed medical doctor. With an exceptional record of verdicts, settlement, and arbitrations awards, Ken has handled cases in California, Florida, and before the United States Supreme Court.

The right attorney can have a tremendous positive impact on the outcome of your impending birth injury claim in Huntington Beach. Kenneth M. Sigelman & Associates offers a unique level of professional attention to your case that you cannot find anywhere else, and the sooner you consult our law firm, the sooner we can put our resources and experience to work for you.  Contact us today  to schedule your free consultation with a Huntington Beach birth injury attorney.

column4: For over 65 years, ADCL has been committed to effectively solving our public agency and private clients’ complex legal issues with excellence, innovation and unwavering determination. We rely on our strong client relationships, our knowledge and experience, and our broad professional network to get the job done at rates significantly lower than those of larger law firms.

Meet Our Attorneys Our attorneys are dedicated to advocating for our clients’ interests and delivering the highest standard of legal service. We invite you to read about our attorneys’ backgrounds and qualifications by visiting  their profiles .
Practice Areas Our firm represents both public and private clients across a range of practice areas. To learn more about our practice, please  click here .
Website Copyright © 2015-2020, Aaronson, Dickerson, Cohn & Lanzone.

column4: A Trusted & Experienced California Law Firm

column8: For more than 25 years, the people and professionals of our state have turned to Rehon & Roberts APC for unparalleled legal services and representation.    As an AV-rated law firm in California’s Silicon Valley, we proudly represent clients in commercial transactions and disputes.
Contact us  today to speak with a knowledgeable professional about your case.
To achieve cost-effective and high-quality results through:

column11: Consistent communication with clients regarding strategies, goals, and results
Thoughtful use of documentation and litigation strategies
Tactful use of alternative dispute resolution procedures
Education, School District, & Other Public Agency Law
Trial & Appellate Court Litigation & Dispute Resolution

column8: The legal professionals at Rehon & Roberts APC have developed extensive knowledge and expertise as a result of our current practice and previous experience, primarily with large law firms. We combine this experience with the advantages of a smaller and more focused law firm to best support our clients in an efficient and cost-effective manner.
© 2021 Rehon & Roberts APC | All Rights Reserved. Website by  Web.com .  Artwork by Carl Jones, Joe Miller, and Dana Roberts.
